race.comment: SATONO INVADER (4) ran on strongly fresh from a spell last start, grabbing second over 1200m at Port Macquarie 3 weeks ago. She has more upside than most in this, and with top hoop Ash Morgan in the irons this time, she is poised to go one better. TALANA (1) showed sharp early speed and sat on the pace last time before fading late to finish a sound sixth over 1250m here a fortnight ago. He is ready to figure in the top 3 this time. FAST BLUE (8) ran on late when finishing third here a fortnight ago, and the extra 112m this time could make all the difference. He cops a wide gate, but he can still have the last say. KHANT FAIL (9) was unplaced two back but improved last run, finishing third over 2200m at Bowraville, after challenging on the last turn. She's stepping up in grade but has the ability to run another bold race.
